\end_inset


\begin_inset Index idx
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
nimbus
\end_layout

\end_inset

) to calculate the derived measurements that result from the use of one
 or more other basic measurements (e.g., potential temperature).
 Since 1993, data from research flights have been archived in NetCDF format
\begin_inset Index idx
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
NetCDF!format
\end_layout

\end_inset

 (cf.
 
\begin_inset Flex URL
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

http://www.unidata.ucar.edu/software/netcdf/docs/
\end_layout

\end_inset

), and the NetCDF header
\begin_inset Index idx
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
NetCDF!header
\end_layout

\end_inset

 for recent projects includes detailed information on the measurements present
 in the file, how they depend on other measurements, units, etc.
 The conventions that the RAF uses for NetCDF data files are documented
 at 
\begin_inset Flex URL
